.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.validationMessage \- HTMLInputElement:
validationMessage property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]validationMessage\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLInputElement\f[R] interface returns a string representing a
localized message that describes the validation constraints that the
\f[CR]<input>\f[R] control does not satisfy (if any).
.PP
If the \f[CR]<input>\f[R] element is not a candidate for constraint
validation (\f[CR]HTMLInputElement.willValidate\f[R] is
\f[CR]false\f[R]), or it satisfies its constraints, the value is the
empty string (\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]).
.PP
If the element is a candidate for constraint validation
(\f[CR]willValidate\f[R] is \f[CR]true\f[R]) and the constraints are not
met (the \f[CR]HTMLInputElement.validity\f[R] object\(cqs
\f[CR]valid\f[R] property is \f[CR]false\f[R]), the value is the error
message that would be shown to the user during validation.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] input = document.getElementById(\(dqmyInput\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] errorMessage = input.validationMessage;
.EE
